# Cedar Kids Therapy triage agent - environment configuration.
#
# Copy this file to `.env` (which is gitignored) and fill in any values
# you want to set locally. The agent works fully without any of these.

# Optional. If set, the agent produces a short natural-language
# "morning huddle" summary on stderr at the end of `npm run triage`
# using Anthropic's Claude (model: claude-haiku-4-5).
#
# If unset, the agent prints a deterministic counts-based summary
# instead. Neither summary affects `output.json` or the audit trace -
# they are stderr-only and the validator does not look at them.
#
# Get a fresh key at https://console.anthropic.com/.
# NEVER paste keys into chat or commit them.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
